#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:116
#, no-c-format
msgid "The command line options are explained below."
msgstr "Kommandolinje-flag bliver forklaret nedenfor."

#. Tag: option
#: index.docbook:120
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid "-c <replaceable>program</replaceable>"
msgid "-c <replaceable>command</replaceable>"
msgstr "-c <replaceable>program</replaceable>"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:121
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid ""
#| "This specifies the program to run as root. It has to be passed in one "
#| "argument. So if, for example, you want to start a new file manager, you "
#| "would enter at the prompt: <userinput><command>kdesu <option>-c "
#| "<replaceable>kfm -sw</replaceable></option></command></userinput>"
msgid ""
"This specifies the command to run as root. It has to be passed in one "
"argument. So if, for example, you want to start a new file manager, you "
"would enter at the prompt: <userinput>$(kf5-config --path "
"libexec)<command>kdesu <option>-c <replaceable> &dolphin;</replaceable></"
"option></command></userinput>"
msgstr ""
"Dette angiver programmet der skal køres som root. Det skal gives som et "
"argument. Så hvis, for eksempel, du ønsker at starte en ny fulhåndtering, "
"vil du skrive ved prompten: <userinput><command>kdesu <option>-c "
"<replaceable>kfm -sw</replaceable></option></command></userinput>"

#. Tag: option
#: index.docbook:127
#, no-c-format
msgid "<option>-d</option>"
msgstr "<option>-d</option>"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:128
#, no-c-format
msgid "Show debug information."
msgstr "Vis fejlinformation."

#. Tag: option
#: index.docbook:131
#, no-c-format
msgid "-f <replaceable>file</replaceable>"
msgstr "-f <replaceable>fil</replaceable>"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:132
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"This option allow efficient use of &kdesu; in <filename>.desktop</filename> "
"files. It tells &kdesu; to examine the file specified by <parameter>file</"
"parameter>. If this file is writable by the current user, &kdesu; will "
"execute the command as the current user. If it is not writable, the command "
"is executed as user <parameter>user</parameter> (defaults to root)."
msgstr ""
"Dette tillader effektiv brug af &kdesu; i <filename>.desktop</filename>-"
"filer. Det beder &kdesu; om at undersøge filen angivet ved <parameter>file</"
"parameter>. Hvis denne fil er skrivbar for nuværende bruger, vil &kdesu; "
"køre kommandoen som nuværende bruger. Hvis dette ikke er tilfældet vil den "
"køres som brugeren <parameter>bruger</parameter> (som standard root)."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:138
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid ""
#| "<parameter>file</parameter> is evaluated like this: if <parameter>FILE</"
#| "parameter> starts with a <literal>/</literal>, it is taken as an absolute "
#| "filename. Otherwise, it is taken as the name of a global &kde; "
#| "configuration file. For example: to configure the K display manager, "
#| "<application>kdm</application>, you could issue <command>kdesu <option>-c "
#| "kdmconfig -f kdmrc</option></command>"
msgid ""
"<parameter>file</parameter> is evaluated like this: if <parameter>file</"
"parameter> starts with a <literal>/</literal>, it is taken as an absolute "
"filename. Otherwise, it is taken as the name of a global &kde; configuration "
"file."
msgstr ""
"<parameter>fil</parameter> bliver evalueret sådan her: hvis <parameter>fil</"
"parameter> begynder med et <literal>/</literal>, tages det som et absolut "
"filnavn. Ellers tages det som navnet på en global &kde; indstillingsfil. For "
"eksempel: for at indstille K skærmhåndteringen, <application>kdm</"
"application>, må du skrive <command>kdesu <option>-c kdmconfig -f kdmrc</"
"option></command>"

#. Tag: term
#: index.docbook:144
#, no-c-format
msgid "<option>-i</option> <replaceable>icon name</replaceable>"
msgstr "<option>-i</option> <replaceable>ikonnavn</replaceable>"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:145
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Specify icon to use in the password dialog. You may specify just the name, "
"without any extension."
msgstr ""
"Angiv ikon at bruge i kodeordsdialogen. Du kan angive kun navnet, uden nogen "
"filendelse."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:147
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid ""
#| "For instance to run <command>kfmclient</command> and show the &konqueror; "
#| "icon in the password dialog:"
